==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chirp
<hw>Chirp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Chirped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Chirping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Of imitative orgin. Cf.
<er>Chirk</er>, <er>Chipper</er>, <er>Cheep</er>, <er>Chirm</er>,
<er>Chirrup</er>.]</ety> <def>To make a shop, sharp, cheerful, as of
small birds or crickets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

